review.reviewBody:
I love the flavor of this pepper jelly! I like it hot, so I left the seeds in the jalapenos. I also prefer to use my kitchen scale to weigh the peppers before putting them in the food processor to mince, so I don't have any waste. The quantities were: 
Red bell (seeded and quartered) 500 grams; 
Green bell (seeded and quartered) 250 grams; 
Jalapeno (halved, seeds not removed) 50 grams. 
I chose to not give all five stars only because I would have liked the jelly less runny. I wonder if I had not simply allowed the mixture to come to a rolling boil for one minute and instead had let it boil until it reached 218-220 degrees F, would I have had better results. I guess I'll try that method next time. It is quite delicious and will be my go to Pepper Jelly recipe, but I will tinker with the jellying.
